6.7.2 Second cross-net variable

if (degxvar!=degxvar2) {
    stats_degx_mean <- ldply(names(fits), 
                 .fun=function(x) { 
                       # Get mean degree by degx group for each simulation
                       temp <- sapply(nodeinfo[[x]], function(simdf) {
                          returndf <- ddply(simdf, .(degx2), 
                                summarise, 
                                meandeg=mean(degree))
                          returnvec <- returndf$meandeg
                          names(returnvec) <- returndf$degx2
                          return(returnvec)
                         })

                       # Get the mean of the mean degrees of each sim
                       means <- round(rowMeans(temp), 2)
                       # Put into a data frame
                       returndf <- data.frame(meandeg=means, degx=names(means),
                                  model=x)


                   
                })

    # Add in observed stats
    numrel <- degtable(egoobj, by=degxvar2, max2=FALSE, wide=FALSE, weighted=TRUE, weighted_N=TRUE)
    obs_stats_degx <- meandeg.by(numrel, by=degxvar2)
    stats_degx_final <- subset(cast(stats_degx_mean , degx~model, value='meandeg'))
    stats_degx_final <- cbind(Observed=obs_stats_degx$MeanDeg, stats_degx_final)
    stats_degx_final <- stats_degx_final[,c(2,1,3:ncol(stats_degx_final))]
    kable(stats_degx_final, caption='Mean degree by cross-network degree') %>%
        kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped", full_width = F) 
}
